From fd70b0e82d00a41937b0c5761a5c727f0735ff92 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 15:53:32 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] chronium: HMAC license-token gate (patch 0020)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Refuse to start without a valid --license-{ts,nonce,token} triple from
the launcher. Defends against extraction of bin/ + DLLs to a different
machine: a pirate who copies the binary off an installed antidetect can
no longer run chrome.exe standalone.

How it works (validated in chrome_browser_main.cc, very early — before
the FingerprintProfile load and any UI):

  token == HMAC_SHA256(BAKED_SECRET, "<ts>|<ppid>" || nonce)[:16]
  abs(now - ts) <= 60 seconds
  ppid == GetParentProcessId(GetCurrentProcessHandle())

All three checks gate. On any failure call std::_Exit(0) — silent
close that looks like a normal crash to the pirate; nothing in the log
hints we explicitly rejected them.

Files:
  chrome/browser/license/license_gate.{h,cc} (new)
  chrome/browser/license/license_secret.h (gitignored — git/info/exclude;
    written by chronium-build/scripts/gen-license-secret.py)
  chrome/browser/chrome_browser_main.cc: EnforceLicenseGate() call
    inserted above the FingerprintProfile loader at line ~1219.
  chrome/browser/BUILD.gn: add license_gate.{h,cc,_secret.h} to chrome
    target sources.
  chrome/common/chrome_switches.{h,cc}: declare kLicenseTs / kLicenseNonce
    / kLicenseToken.

Pairs with chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.cc which
already loads the per-launch fingerprint JSON; we now also encrypt the
JSON itself in the launcher and decrypt before that load, so even if
the gate is somehow bypassed, the fingerprint library stays opaque
without the secret. See antidetect/backend/app/engine/license.py and
chronium-build/scripts/encrypt-profiles.py for the launcher side.

BoringSSL HMAC_SHA256 was already linked — no new deps. Token compares
in constant time (span-based ConstantTimeEqual) to avoid timing
side-channels.
